    "narrative": "The Austin Waves head into today\u2019s slate with **Gunnar Henderson** as our clear offensive anchor; his massive 81.88 score is buoyed by a prime leadoff spot and a 16% park factor advantage, making him a locked-in elite play against the favorable matchup. **Kyle Tucker** (72.86) remains a high-end start despite the pending lineup, as his strong xwOBA and the added wind-out incentive at his home park create a high ceiling for both R and HR production. We are also leaning heavily into our speed-focused targets today: **Luis Robert Jr.** (62.21) provides a massive secondary benefit due to the opposing pitcher\u2019s slow delivery, which significantly inflates his theft potential, while **Josh Lowe** (65.92) serves as a strong play because the combination of dynamic platoon advantages and favorable wind conditions pushes him well into the \"Strong\" start tier.\n\nOur bench strategy centers on the discipline of keeping game caps in check. **Nasim Nunez** (38.00) was the primary consideration for a spot start, but he failed to clear the 40-point floor threshold necessitated by a difficult matchup against Skenes. His utility is further suppressed by the opponent\u2019s elite catcher pop time, which limits his stolen base ceiling. Elsewhere, we are navigating health hurdles as we await returns from **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** and **Jackson Merrill**, who are unavailable today, and **Jordan Westburg**, who remains on the IL. We will monitor the status of **Josh Jung** and **Andy Pages** closely; both are currently penciled into the lineup pending final confirmation, but their scores (58.22 and 62.75, respectively) remain robust enough that we expect them to retain their spots even if shuffling occurs.",
